cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI 

This paper discusses the use of data mining and predictive analysis in healthcare, specifically in the context of electronic health records. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which includes topics related to the intersection of computing and social issues, including healthcare. The sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely, as the paper discusses the use of clinical decision support systems driven by live data, which involves interaction between humans and computers. The use of predictive analysis and data mining also suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning), as well as cs.DB (Databases) for the management and analysis of large amounts of health-related data. Finally, the paper's focus on predicting treatment outcomes suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which includes topics related to intelligent systems and decision-making.
